 {"id":"bd-3co7k.3.3","title":"Swipe Gestures for Horizontal Scrolling","description":"# Swipe Gestures for Horizontal Scrolling

## Problem Statement
Horizontal scrollable areas (carousels, feature grids on mobile) rely on native 
scroll behavior. Adding explicit swipe gesture support with snap points and 
visual feedback creates a more native-feeling experience.

## Background
**Current State:**
- Stepper component has swipe support via @use-gesture/react
- Other horizontal scrollable areas use CSS scroll-snap
- No visual indicator of swipe progress or direction

**@use-gesture/react Usage (stepper.tsx ~line 169-193):**
```tsx
const bind = useDrag(
  ({ movement: [mx], velocity: [vx], direction: [dx], cancel }) => {
    // Handle swipe logic
  },
  { axis: "x", filterTaps: true }
);
```

## Implementation Details

### Step 1: Identify Swipeable Areas
Review the app for horizontal scrollable content:
1. Mobile feature cards on landing page
2. Tool categories on /tldr or /tools (if horizontal)
3. Lesson cards on /learn (mobile)
4. Any carousel components

### Step 2: Create useSwipeScroll Hook
```typescript
// apps/web/lib/hooks/useSwipeScroll.ts

import { useRef, useCallback } from "react";
import { useDrag } from "@use-gesture/react";
import { useReducedMotion } from "./useReducedMotion";

interface UseSwipeScrollOptions {
  /** Minimum swipe distance to trigger navigation */
  threshold?: number;
  /** Items per "page" for snap calculation */
  itemsPerPage?: number;
  /** Callback when page changes */
  onPageChange?: (page: number) => void;
}

export function useSwipeScroll(options: UseSwipeScrollOptions = {}) {
  const {
    threshold = 50,
    itemsPerPage = 1,
    onPageChange,
  } = options;

  const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
  const prefersReducedMotion = useReducedMotion();
  const [currentPage, setCurrentPage] = useState(0);

  const scrollToPage = useCallback((page: number) => {
    if (!containerRef.current) return;

    const container = containerRef.current;
    const itemWidth = container.scrollWidth / totalItems;
    const targetScroll = page * itemWidth * itemsPerPage;

    container.scrollTo({
      left: targetScroll,
      behavior: prefersReducedMotion ? "auto" : "smooth",
    });

    setCurrentPage(page);
    onPageChange?.(page);
  }, [itemsPerPage, prefersReducedMotion, onPageChange]);

  const bind = useDrag(
    ({ movement: [mx], velocity: [vx], direction: [dx], last }) => {
      if (!last) return;

      const shouldNavigate = Math.abs(mx) > threshold || Math.abs(vx) > 0.5;
      if (!shouldNavigate) return;

      const nextPage = dx < 0 ? currentPage + 1 : currentPage - 1;
      scrollToPage(Math.max(0, nextPage));
    },
    { axis: "x", filterTaps: true, pointer: { touch: true } }
  );

  return {
    containerRef,
    bind,
    currentPage,
    scrollToPage,
  };
}
```

### Step 3: Add Visual Swipe Indicator
Show dots or line indicator for current position:
```tsx
function SwipeIndicator({ current, total }: { current: number; total: number }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex justify-center gap-1.5 mt-4">
      {Array.from({ length: total }).map((_, i) => (
        <div
          key={i}
          className={cn(
